#Text=Gotland
#Text=Gotland is Sweden 's largest island , in the middle of the Baltic Sea .
#Text=Some 50,000 people live here all year .
#Text=Together with some minor islands it forms the Gotland province , Gotland Municipality and Gotland County .
#Text=With a peculiar dialect , a glorious history and a scenery very different from mainland Sweden , the island has a spirit of independence .
#Text=Cities
#Text=— the only city , around 20,000 inhabitants , crowded during summers .

#Text=Is on UNESCO 's World Heritage list as an " outstanding example of a Northern European walled Hanseatic town which has in a unique way preserved its townscape and its extremely valuable buildings , which in form and function clearly reflect this significant human settlement " .

column1: #Text=Regions and minor islands
#Text=Northern Gotland including Slite and Fårösund as well as the Lummelunda cave .
#Text=Central Gotland including Roma and Klintehamn
#Text=Southern Gotland including Ljugarn and Burgsvik
#Text=— A smaller island just off the northern coast of the main island .
#Text=Known for its high concentration of rauks and sand beaches .
#Text=— A national park island north of Gotland .
#Text=—
#Text=The islands of Stora Karlsö and Lilla Karlsö are definitely worth a day 's visit , Stora Karlsö is one of the world 's oldest nature preserves , second only to Yellowstone National Park .
#Text=Situated outside of Klintehamn .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Gotland is said to be the homeland of the legendary Goths , who migrated through Central Europe sacked the Roman Empire during the 5th century AD .
#Text=Medieval Gotland language has many similarities with the Gothic language , though there are no first-hand historical records that the Goths really came from Gotland .
#Text=In its early history , Gotland was an independent kingdom and still today , the older generations do not regard themselves as Swedes - they are nothing but Gotlanders .
#Text=Gotland was a central location of the Viking Age of the 8th to 11th centuries .
#Text=While the true Vikings ( pirates or mercenaries ) were not from Gotland , many people on the island were sailing merchants ; farmaðr .
#Text=During the Hanseatic period in the Middle Ages , Visby and Gotland was an important stop on the trade routes on the Baltic Sea .
#Text=The island lost its role after a Danish war in the 14th century .

#Text=One of the best-known events of the island 's history was Danish king Valdemar Atterdag 's ransom for Visby , where he demanded large amounts of gold and silver to spare the city from being burnt down .
#Text=The written records are unreliable , though .
#Text=As the Hanseatic League lost importance , the Danes took control over the island for 300 years , ending Gotland 's golden age .
#Text=The Dano-Swedish wars of the 16th and 17th centuries gave Sweden the dominant power of the Baltic Sea , including Gotland .
#Text=The island was a poor backwater until the late 19th century , as cement manufacturing , tourism and military presence gave the island a renaissance .
#Text=Swedish filmmaker Ingmar Bergman recorded many films on Gotland and the surrounding smaller islands , especially Fårö .
#Text=The island holds many medieval memories ; old farmlands and more than 90 churches , all with different architecture .
#Text=Talk
#Text=The Gotland dialect is remarkable and is easy to recognize .
#Text=Still , the islanders understand standard Swedish , and virtually everyone but the oldest speaks English .
#Text=By plane
#Text=Visby Airport ( VBY ) ( just north of Visby ) .
#Text=The easiest way to get to the city centre is by taxi .
#Text=There is a special reduced price for travelling the airport-city centre .
#Text=Approx . 10 minutes .
#Text=There are flights all year to Visby from Stockholm , Gothenburg and Linköping .
#Text=During summer , there 's also flights from Oslo and Ängelholm .
#Text=A flight from Stockholm takes about 25 minutes , from Gothenburg about 50 minutes .
#Text=By boat
#Text=Destination Gotland runs ferries from Nynäshamn and Oskarshamn to Visby all year .
#Text=You can also bring your car .
#Text=This is the cheapest way to get to the island .
#Text=The ferry takes about three hours .
#Text=The harbour is in the very centre of Visby .
#Text=Gotland is a natural destination for boating on the Baltic Sea .
#Text=Safe natural harbours are few if any , but there is an adequate number of guest harbours spread along the coasts , the most busy in Visby centre .
#Text=Several international cruise lines call at Gotland .
#Text=Get around
#Text=The easiest way to see the island is by car .
#Text=There are several car rentals in Visby .
#Text=There are also bus services from Visby to all parts of the island , but be sure to bring a timetable before you leave Visby , since many bus stops are served only a few times per day .
#Text=See Kollektivtrafiken and Resrobot ( a search engine for all public transport inside Sweden ) .
#Text=Gotland is Sweden 's largest island , but still only about 120 km from north to south and 50 km across , and with relatively short distances between different sites of interest .
#Text=Most roads are paved and the hills are few .
#Text=Therefore , cycling is an alternative to driving .
#Text=Bikes can be brought from mainland on the ferry , or rented at arrival to the island ( or later , if you go to a suitable location ) .
#Text=See
#Text=There are over 90 medieval churches on the island .
#Text=Most of them have n't been modernised since the 15th century .
#Text=Rauks
#Text=Fantastic rock formations ( Raukar ) are found along the island 's coast .
#Text=These natural sculptures are made out of lime stone and created as surrounding " softer " minerals have been eroded by the sea .
#Text=Asunden rauk field ( By Slite in the north-eastern of Gotland ) .
#Text=A barren island , connected to the Gotland mainland by a bridge , with a large rauk field .
#Text=Bjärge rauk field ( Located on Fårö ) .
#Text=The largest rauk field on Gotland .
#Text=Gamle hamn rauk field ( Located on Fårö ) .
#Text=Also contains a viking era burial field .
#Text=Hammarshage hällar and Holmshällars rauk fields ( In the southern part of Gotland ) .
#Text=Two nearby rauk fields .
#Text=Hoburgsgubben ( On the southernmost tip of Gotland ) .
#Text=The rauk is said to resemble a human face in profile from the right angle .
#Text=Kyllaj rauk field ( In north-eastern Gotland ) .
#Text=Langhammars rauk field ( Located on Fårö ) .
#Text=Lergrav and Husken rauk fields ( On the north-eastern shore of Gotland ) .
#Text=Two nearby rauk fields .
#Text=Lickershamn rauk field and " Jungfrun " , Lickershamn ( Approx . 25 km north of Visby ) .
#Text=There is a minor rauk-field by the village Lickershamn .
#Text=However , the rauk " Jungfrun " , located some 500 meters from Lickershamn , is the largest rauk on Gotland .
